# Cloudflare Pages deploy

**Live site:** https://costco-chaos.pages.dev

## Always deploy to production

`wrangler pages deploy` without `--branch main` creates a **preview** deployment only. Production stays on the old build (users see stale assets, e.g. missing GLBs).

```bash
# ✅ Correct — updates costco-chaos.pages.dev
npm run deploy

# ✅ Equivalent
npm run build:cf && npx wrangler pages deploy dist --project-name costco-chaos --branch main

# ❌ Wrong — preview only, production unchanged
npx wrangler pages deploy dist --project-name costco-chaos
```

## Workflow after shippable changes

1. `npm run build` (or `validate:routes` when touching nav)
2. Commit + push to GitHub (`main` or merge feature branch to `main`)
3. `npm run deploy` — must use `--branch main` (wired in `package.json`)

## Build base path

- **Cloudflare / production:** `VITE_BASE=/` via `build:cf` — never bare `npm run build` for deploy
- **Local dev:** default `/costco-chaos/` in `vite.config.ts`

## Verify production

```bash
curl -sI https://costco-chaos.pages.dev/models/cars/prius.glb | grep content-type
# expect: model/gltf-binary (not text/html)
```
